<br><h2><div align="center">To qualify for membership to British Airways Virtual the pilot is required to meet the following minimum criteria.</div></h2>
<br>


<h3>Rules &amp; Regulations</h3>

<br>


<br>
<div align="center">The pilot must be in possession of Flight Simulator 2004/FSX or X-Plane.</div>
<br>
<div align="center">The pilot must be over the age of 14.</div>
<br>

<div align="center">The ability to fly for British Airways Virtual once every 30 days.</div>
<br>
<div align="center">The pilot must submit their real identity and a valid e-mail address.</div>
<br>
<div align="center">The must show professionalism within the organization and when conducting Online Operations.</div>
<br>
<div align="center">All registrations must be submitted by the pilot applying not by anyone else on behalf of the applying pilot</div>
<br>
<div align="center">Although there is no obligation to fly on a network, pilots must have a VATSIM and/or IVAO account which is active.</div>
<br>
<div align="center">Pilots must not be abusive or threatening towards other pilots or staff. Failure to comply will result in being removed from the virtual airline without notice.</div>
<br>
<div align="center">We retain the right to remove any pilot from the virtual airline at any time for any reason we deem fit.</div>
<br>
<div align="center">Flights must have a touchdown rate of -500fpm or less and must not make a loss of more than £20,000 or the flight will be rejected (except if a valid reason is given e.g. Flight sim freezes on touchdown)</div>
<br>
<h3>New Pilots</h3>
<br>
<br>
<div align="center">New pilots must complete their first flight within 7 days of registration.</div>
<br>
<div align="center">New pilots cannot request Leave of Absence until they have completed <b>five</b> flights with us <b>which were accepted</b>.</div>
<br>
<div align="center">New pilots will be closely monitored by Chief Operating Officer for the first 14 days within the virtual airline.</div>
<br>
<div align="center">New applicants should have a response from us within 24-48 hours.</div>
<br>
<div align="center">After registration is completed, new pilots must sign up with the forum and may join the Facebook group.</div>
<br>
<div align="center">Pilots are required to sit the SOP (Standard Operations Procedures) Exam to be able to rank up from Trainee to Junior First Officer.</div>
<br>
<br>
<h3>Pilot Inactivity</h3>
<br>
<br>
<div align="center">Pilots who do not complete one flight every 30 days will be removed from the virtual airline without prior notice.</div>
<br>
<div align="center">Pilots are allowed 90 days Leave of Absence (LOA) per calander year. 90 days LoA are reset on the 1st of January each year.</div>
<br>
<div align="center">Pilots can request Special Leave of Absence (SLOA). This must be set in writing to either HR, CEO, VCEO or COO.</div>
<br>
<div align="center">Pilots requiring LoA (Leave of Absence), will need to apply for it via the website (Operations tab or Pilot profile page).</div>
<br>
<br>
<h3>Staff Inactivity</h3>
<br>
<div align="center">Staff who do not come on Teamspeak at least once per week will be warned and if it continues, they will lose their job.</div>
<br>
<div align="center">Staff who do not do their job will be warned and then they will lose their job.</div>
<br>
<div align="center">Staff are entitled to Special Leave of Absence (SLOA) which can only be arranged with the CEO, Vice CEO or the COO.</div>
<br>
<div align="center">Staff are also required to fly once every 30 days.</div>
<br>
